text: Kanjut Sar is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in Pakistan. It is also sometimes spelled Kunjudh Sar. Kanjut Sar is part of the Hispar Muztagh subrange. It is the 26th highest mountain in the world. The first person to reach the top was Camillo Pellissier in 1959. ==References== Category:Mountains of Gilgit-Baltistan Category:Karakoram
